<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-79-0876 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper reviews the South African coal industry. After a brief examinationof production and consumption statistics the export market is discussed.Exports account for only about one quarter of the total production inSouth Africa, it is the domestic market which is especially important.This market is discussed in terms of four sectors: electricity; metallurgical;synfuels and petrochemicals; and industrial. Finally, factors expectedto have an impact on the future of the South African coal industry arediscussed. These include politics, domestic industry structure and finance,inflation, currency values, the international market and sanctions. Thepaper concludes that while the domestic market growth should continueto grow there are factors affecting the export market which are totallyout of the control of the South African coal industry. 6 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>